item.name: sieStAgentType
item.description: Type of agent (i.e. 'Desktop' or 'Server'). This field can be used to launch the correct management front end application (DeskView or ServerView) in enterprise management systems.

item.name: sieStNumberComponents
item.description: Number of available components; this is the number of entries in the component table

item.name: sieStNumberSubsystems
item.description: Number of available subsystems; this is the number of entries in the subsystem table

item.name: sieStSystemIdentify
item.description: Sets the signal IDENTIFY for the system: off(1): clear the identify signal / signal is off on(2): set the IDENTIFY signal not-available(3): identify signal ist not available (this value cannot be set) blinking(4): IDENTIFY LED blinking, used for different purposes Setting IDENTIFY by the ServerView application normally sets a LED to have the possibility to identify a system selected by ServerView.

item.name: sieStSubsystemList
item.description: List if subsystems included in this system, separated by blank spaces. E.g. 'Environment PowerSupply MassStorage'

item.name: sieStSystemLastErrorMessage
item.description: Error message text of the component that has failed last. Empty string, if no error has happened since reboot. This object is not supported by all components and can therefore be empty although an error happened.

item.name: sieStSystemStatusValue
item.description: Overall status of this system: ok(1): all subsystems and components working properly, no failure degraded(2): redundant components failed or signal a warning error(3): severe problem, system may no longer work properly failed(4): this value is obsolete - will no longer appear unknown(5): none of the subsystems had a valid status (e.g. during initialization)

item.name: sieStAgentBuild
item.description: Build time and date of agent program implementation

item.name: sieStAgentVersionString
item.description: Agent version string <Major>.<Minor> (i.e. 1.05)

item.name: sieStAgentCompany
item.description: Agent company name

item.name: sieStAgentId
item.description: Agent identification string

item.name: svOsNumberPartitions
item.description: Number of available system partitions (1 for standalone systems)

item.name: svOsAgentInterface
item.description: The interface this agent is listening at

item.name: svOsAgentBuild
item.description: Compilation time and date of agent program

item.name: svOsAgentVersion
item.description: Agent's version string (e.g. 1.05)

item.name: svOsAgentCompany
item.description: Agent's company name (e.g. Fujitsu Technology Solutions)

item.name: svOsAgentId
item.description: Agent identification string
